column2: Morgan Stanley Emerging Markets Debt Fund Inc

Morgan Stanley Emerging Markets Debt Fund, Inc. (the Fund) is a non-diversified, closed-end management investment company. The Fund's primary investment objective is to produce high current income and as a secondary objective, to seek capital appreciation, through investments primarily in debt securities of government and government-related issuers located in emerging countries, of entities organized to restructure outstanding debt of such issuers and debt securities of corporate issuers in or organized under the laws of emerging countries. The Fund's portfolio of investments include fixed income securities, warrants and short-term investments. The Fund's investment advisor is Morgan Stanley Investment Management Inc., which is a subsidiary of Morgan Stanley.
